    rectoEn: 'The physical settlement of a reverse convertible: mechanics and psychological effect?',
    versoEn: 'Below the strike, the client receives 100/K shares per 100 of notional — at a 100 strike, one share worth S_T. It is exactly the put seller\'s payoff: "buying" at 100 (his notional) a share worth less. Cash settlement — 100 − (K − S_T) — is economically IDENTICAL, psychologically very different: receiving shares feeds the illusion that "you just have to wait for it to come back". Reading landmarks: gain capped at the coupon as soon as S_T ≥ K, break-even at 100 − coupon.',
